text: Multifurca zonaria is a species of mushroom-forming fungus in the genus Russulaceae. Originally described from Thailand as a Russula species in 2003, it was moved to the newly created genus Multifurca in 2008. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:Russulales Category:Fungi described in 2003 Category:Fungi of Asia
title: Multifurca zonaria
